description: Concatenates five attributes to create CAS_ID
No horizontal structure so structure percent is 100

Count layers up to max_layer_number which is set by the createMappingsView() function in the workflow. Third grouping represents nfl rows using slu (from FOREST table), water_code (from WATERBODY table), and wc (from WETLAND table). slu and water_code rows will be translated using the NFL table. wc rows will be translated using the ECO table. Dummy names used where values need to be mapped to two different attributes.
Maps source value to CROWN_CLOSURE_UPPER using lists of values
Maps source value to CROWN_CLOSURE_LOWER using lists of values
Correct translation has not been determined.
Maps source value to SPECIES_1 using lookup table
Maps source value to SPECIES_PER_1 by multiplying by 10
Maps source value to SPECIES_2 using lookup table
Maps source value to SPECIES_PER_2 by multiplying by 10
Maps source value to SPECIES_3 using lookup table
Maps source value to SPECIES_PER_3 by multiplying by 10
Maps source value to SPECIES_4 using lookup table
Maps source value to SPECIES_PER_4 by multiplying by 10
